   integrated system suggests that the base stock list price policy fails
   to achieve optimality even under deterministic demand. Instead, the
   optimal policy is characterized by two critical values: a reorder point
   and a target safety stock. Under this policy, a positive order is issued
   if and only if the inventory level is below the reorder point. When this
   happens, the optimal order and price are coordinated to achieve a
   constant target safety stock, which aims at hedging the demand
   uncertainty. We further investigate the profit improvement obtained from
