   brands toward larger ones following periods of poor financial
   performance. This indicates the behavior is determined by parties above
   brand managers in the firm. These findings are consistent with firms
   engaging in real earnings management and suggest that effects on
   subsequent reporting periods and competitor behavior are greater than
