   single period to produce. An accepted order must be filled before a
   positive delivery lead time. The underlying order acceptance decisions
   involve trade-offs between committing resources (production capacity and
   component inventory) to low-reward firm orders and reserving resources
   for high-reward orders. We develop a Markov chain model that captures
   the key characteristics of pseudo orders, including demand lumpiness,
