   order acceptance policy is characterized by class prioritization,
   resource-imbalance-based rationing, and capacity-inventory-demand
   matching. In particular, the rationing level for each class is
   determined by a critical value that depends on the resource imbalance
   level, defined as the net difference between the production capacity and
   component inventory levels. Extensive numerical tests underscore the
   importance of the key properties of the optimal policy and provide
   operational and managerial insights on the value of the short-term
   demand forecast and the robustness of the optimal policy.
