   the imperfect waiting list information as published currently into the
   patient's decision making. We analyze structural properties of this
   model. In particular, we establish conditions that guarantee a monotone
   value function and a threshold-type optimal policy with respect to the
   partially observable rank state that captures the imperfect waiting list
   information. Furthermore, we develop an improved solution methodology to
   solve a generic POMDP model. This solution method guarantees, for any
   fixed grid, the best possible approximation to the optimal value
